description:
&lt;p&gt;The Plastics Outpatients is based within Outpatient West at the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are a busy outpatients department undertaking the assessment and care of patients. It is a progressive and exciting department which is continuously adapting to meet and enhance the care provided to our patients and we are seeking a motivated and enthusiastic person who is keen to join the team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Wound care experience is desirable.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As post holder, you will work in the nurse led clinic, assessing, implementing and altering courses of treatment for patients who have undergone plastic and reconstructive surgery for either trauma or elective circumstances. You will also assist with minor surgery procedures carried out within the department. Extended roles which can be undertaken with experience include tissue expansion and seroma drainage.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly and supportive working atmosphere.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work in an interesting and challenging environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work as a member of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist in minor surgery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant post registration training and courses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in plastic surgery is desirable but training can be given.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of wound care and aseptic technique essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to be flexible and work as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To have excellent interpersonal/communication and organisational skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** The department is currently open Monday – Friday, 8am – 6pm. Occasional evening and weekend work is also undertaken. **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time:&lt;/strong&gt; 17.25 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 29th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Britta Andersen - Deputy Sister&lt;/p&gt;
